//It is a simple-looking but interesting question about the distribution of 
watermelon b/w 2 people,the weights when distributing should an even number like
if watermelon weights 100kg then both the guys will have 50,50kg of watermelon
which is an "even" distribution so yeah that will print "YES" for 100 kg watermelon

Note:It will print "YES" for every even weight but not for 2 kg because when distributing
2 kg it becomes 1kg on both sides which is "odd" distribution


Solution:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
 
int main() {
    int w;
    cin >> w;
    if (w % 2 == 0 && w > 2) {
        cout << "YES";
    } else {
        cout << "NO";
    }
    return 0;
}
